{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1d2bbd80-2b70-466d-ad55-cba6b9dea75c","content":"\n\nTo register your MCP server in the official **MCP Registry** (hosted at [github.com/modelcontextprotocol/registry](https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/registry)):\n\n1. **Fork** the `modelcontextprotocol/registry` repo on GitHub.\n2. **Add a JSON file** for your server under the `servers/` directory (e.g., `servers/your-server-name.json`) following the registry's schema — typically including:\n   - `name`, `description`, `repository` URL\n   - `packages` (e.g., your NuGet package ID/URL)\n   - `capabilities` (tools, resources, prompts your server exposes)\n3. **Open a Pull Request** against the main branch.\n4. The maintainers will review and merge it.\n\nCheck the existing entries in `servers/` for the exact schema and required fields, as it may evolve. The repo's `README.md` or `CONTRIBUTING.md` will have the latest submission guidelines.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2ecbac34-9faf-4d2e-820e-36516b706a4b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to register their C# MCP server in the official MCP Registry. This is a general knowledge question about the MCP (Model Context Protocol) ecosystem. Let me provide what I know and also check for any relevant information online.","outputTokens":307},"id":"881c324b-93be-41d8-8d70-7e5c19dede44","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:43:22.027Z","parentId":"01fc20d5-193e-4c70-9895-30ee4c605574"}
